Brett Sawyer - Industrial Mayhem\
a.) Five unique geometry nodes - Complete \
The five simple physics components/geometry nodes are delineated by Unity 3D physics capabilities including:\
(1) Simple collider on a rigid body to allow interaction between game player and object. In this case the simple collider is a cardboard box made from a Unite cube primitive with a mass of 1 kg. When in contact with the 80 kg game player object an appropriate collision between the objects occurs.\
(2) Trigger collider with the game player object that results in an added force to rigid body objects. In this case a collider game object is set to trigger environment behavior. When the player enters the trigger region 10 kg drums are pushed by and added force to enable these objects to start rolling toward the player down a set of stairs.\
(3) Cloth physics. In this case cloth physic components are assigned to a double plane game object. This said game object is used to simulate a wind force in the environment due to HVAC characteristic of the proposed industrial setting \
(4) Soft body physics. A soft body, inelastic collision object is simulated using cloth physics combined with rigid body physics. In this case a rigid body is set inside a sphere primitive with painted cloth constraints. This allows for soft body type collisions when coming in contact with other rigid body components in the environment.\
(5) Rigid body added force at contact. In this case to support the aforementioned game feel of urgency or mayhem. Rigid body components on the player and a table were used to with colliders to allow the player to flip these objects. This is achieved by adding a force to the table rigid body at the point of contact between this rigid body and the player.\
\
b.) Two compound objects - Complete\
The two compound objects consisted of a hinge joint physics component. The implementations of these hinge joints differ in behavior.\
(1) Spring hinge enabled joint. In this case a spring hinge joint is setup between a door post and swinging gate. This is typical of the industrial setting where these signs can provide access control\'97motivation for the spring back behavior.\
(2) Motor hinge enabled joint. In this case a motor enabled joint was used to implement a large industrial fan. This fan is made up of five capsule collider primitives where the project hierarchy is used to maintain fan like behavior of the rotating capsule objects. \
\
c.) Variable terrain - Complete\
Variable terrain was implemented using the ProBuilder basic asset available for scene development in Unity. Ramps and platforms are implemented using this GUI scene builder software. Due to the needed overhaul of the animation controller and known bugs with the jump function of the animation controller, graduated steps are not included to improve game feel and will be updated in subsequent controller work and debugging.\
\
d.) Material sounds - Complete\
Multiple audio sources throughout the industrial environment are used to improve player interaction with a activity rich game garden environment. \
\
Due to the chosen theme, surfaces are limited to concrete and grated steel platforms. When the player navigates the grated platforms and appropriated footstep audio source is enabled.\
\
Other audio sources are tied to geometry nodes listed above. For example, when the player flips the table a loud wood knocking audio is enabled. Furthermore, when the player triggers a trap of gas drums rolling down the steps, and appropriated steel drum rolling audio is enabled.\
\
Note all sounds bytes were acquired using www.freesound.org\
\
e.) Game feel - Complete\
As mentioned above, the chosen theme defined interactions between the player and the industrial environment. This game feel was enhanced by high density interaction through the garden level and the player. The feeling of the industrial environment is conveyed to the user through physics animations that combine large HVAC system simulation with sound components. The garden feel object layout is such that the order of an industrial environment is conveyed. In doing so, all objects are interactive with appropriate physics reactions. This includes table flipping to convey the sense of mayhem in the player.  \
